 I think its comming  soon.<br>
Next generation perhaps not, but surely the one that will bring the change to space propulsion and the way we travel across the vastness of Space must be founded, in my view, on the alteration of the fabric of Space-time.. not so much Science ficition any more, its just that it dwells right now in the theoretical waters.<br>
The theory is based on the fact that all matter as we know it (or maters for the purpose) is governed at the macroscopic level by the Gravitational force. This is the force we must overcome in order to cover huge distances in shorter times. <br>
Gravitational force is but the bending of Space-time by massive bodies. (Einstein's General Relativity)<br>
The logic is that if we can alter the structure of Space-time then we can travel without propulsion as we know it. The way its being looked at is that ultimately matter is made of electrically charged entities which in combination become neutral, but if we could alter that equilibrium then we would be altering the structure at the macroscopic level. So the answer lies within  a deeper understanding of the essence of the electromagnetic fields however the key lies in the discovery of the link between both universal interactions: the gravitational and the electronmagnetic. If we get to understand how they interact then we can solve the puzzle and a breakthought will come then as to no propulsion needed..<br>
Just bend space-time at your will <br>
while you keep your scape craft still...<br>
